## Context
The spec describes a `ready` command that finds open tickets whose
Blocked-by references all point to closed tickets (transitive
closure). This is the only query needing code beyond grep. No
implementation exists.

## Relevant files
- `scripts/validate_tickets.py` — reuse ticket parser from vt
- `scripts/ready_tickets.py` — new script
- `Makefile` — add `ticket-ready` target

## Actions
1. Extract ticket parser from `validate_tickets.py` into shared
   module (`scripts/ticket_parser.py`) or reuse inline.
2. Write `scripts/ready_tickets.py`:
   - Parse all tickets in `tickets/`
   - Build dependency graph from Blocked-by headers
   - Compute ready set: open tickets where every Blocked-by
     target has Status: closed (or doesn't exist — treat missing
     as satisfied, with warning)
   - Output: one ticket Id per line (greppable), or `--json` for
     structured output
3. Add `ticket-ready` target to Makefile

## Test
First test: `test_ready_tickets.py`
- Open ticket with no blockers → ready
- Open ticket blocked by closed ticket → ready
- Open ticket blocked by open ticket → not ready
- Transitive: A blocked by B, B blocked by C (open) → A not ready

## Verification
- [ ] `make ticket-ready` lists currently unblocked tickets
- [ ] Output matches manual grep analysis

## Exit criteria
- `make ticket-ready` works correctly on existing tickets
- Handles edge cases (missing refs, circular deps with warning)
